# ============================================================================
# COMMENT ON RULES
# ============================================================================

# Node.js & npm:
#   - Packages in node_modules/ should not be committed
#   - Lock files should be committed for reproducible installs
#   - Remove "package-lock.json" from ignore if using npm for exact versioning

# Build outputs:
#   - Compiled JavaScript files are generated, don't commit
#   - Webpack bundles are generated
#   - TypeScript output files (.d.ts, .js.map) are generated

# IDE:
#   - IDE configurations are personal, don't commit
#   - .vscode/ contains personal settings
#   - .idea/ contains IntelliJ settings

# OS:
#   - OS-specific files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db) aren't project files

# Secrets:
#   - Never commit API keys, credentials, or secrets
#   - Use .env files for local secrets (add to .gitignore)

# Testing:
#   - Coverage reports are generated
#   - Test artifacts don't need version control

# Environment:
#   - Local .env files are user-specific, don't commit
#   - Build artifacts are generated

# ============================================================================
# TO USE THIS FILE:
# ============================================================================

# 1. Place this file in the root of your RedBlink repository
# 2. Git automatically respects it
# 3. To check what would be ignored: git status --ignored
# 4. To add a file that's ignored: git add -f filename
# 5. To remove from ignoring: Edit this file and remove the pattern

# ============================================================================
# HELPFUL GIT COMMANDS
# ============================================================================

# View all ignored files:
#   git status --ignored

# Check if specific file would be ignored:
#   git check-ignore -v path/to/file

# Ignore file that was previously tracked:
#   git rm --cached filename

# Add ignored file anyway:
#   git add -f filename

# ============================================================================
